<subSubSection id="76C4F5543F14DF010C8A2638D24D10AE" type="description">
<paragraph id="060CF77FEF688D5FC44A16CDD1907B63" pageNumber="3">Description: Morphometric data given in Table 1. Male larger than male, largest male 22.2 mm SL. Dorsal profile slightly convex from snout to end of dorsal-fin base, approximately straight on caudal peduncle. Ventral profile convex on head, almost straight to gently convex from anterior portion of venter to end of anal-fin base, nearly straight on caudal peduncle. Body slender, subcylindrical anteriorly, slightly wider than deep, to compressed posteriorly. Greatest body depth at level of pelvic-fin base.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79DAEA426C2F458DC140C2B18B1F9495" pageNumber="4">Tip of dorsal and anal fins rounded. Caudal fin rounded. Pectoral fin rounded, posterior margin on vertical anterior to pelvic-fin base. Tip of pelvic fin reaching between urogenital papilla and base of 1st anal-fin ray in male, and reaching anus in female. Pelvic-fin bases in close proximity. Dorsal-fin origin on vertical through base of last anal-fin ray or slightly posterior to anal-fin base, between neural spines of 20th and 21st vertebrae. Analfin origin between pleural ribs of 15th and 16th vertebra. Dorsal-fin rays 6-7; anal-fin rays 9-10; caudal-fin rays 23-24; pectoral-fin rays 12; pelvic-fin rays 6.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1FFE0A7B07C42825ED9842697503DC87" pageNumber="4">Scales large, cycloid. Body and head entirely scaled, except anterior ventral surface of head. Few scales on caudal-fin base; no scales on dorsal and anal fins. Frontal squamation S-patterned; E-scales not overlapping medially; scales arranged in transverse pattern, all scales with exposed posterior margin. Longitudinal series of scales 31-33; transverse series of scales 7; scale rows around caudal peduncle 16. Ctenii-like contact organ on each scale of anteroventral portion of male flank. Supraorbital neuromasts 3 + 3; last neuromast of anterior supraorbital series separated by interspace occupied by scale. Preopercular canal absent.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F525AF20373A0F35AF259308B89CE1BB" pageNumber="4">Interhyal vestigial, not ossified. Five branchiostegal rays. Second pharyngobranchial teeth absent. Gill-rakers of first branchial arch 1 + 6. Vomerine teeth absent. Desmosphenotic absent. Ventral process of posttemporal absent. Total vertebrae 31-32.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="20B7B1BF4DB08FB54472A37668C629D1" pageNumber="5">Coloration: Male: Side of body light brown, with longitudinal rows of red, dark brown and light blue dots. Dorsum light brown, venter light gray. Side of head dark reddish brown with light purple dots. Infraorbital region and ventral surface of head light gray; transverse black bar on chin. Iris green, dorsal portion of orbit bright silver. Dorsal fin light yellow with broad black median stripe. Anal fin bright yellow, base light blue. Caudal fin dark gray with distal white bar; basal portion with light gray and black dots. Pelvic fin yellow. Pectoral fin hyaline.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="60652FCAEE978D1AD4148105D97D5B03" pageNumber="5">Female: Side of body light brown with six narrow dark brown stripes. Dorsum light brown, venter pink. Side of head light brown with dark brown dots. Infraorbital region and ventral surface of head light pink; transverse dark brown bar on chin. Iris yellow, dorsal portion of orbit bright silver. Dorsal fin hyaline with gray median stripe. Anal fin yellow to pale orange. Caudal fin hyaline with small dark gray spots on basal portion. Pelvic fin pale orange. Pectoral fin hyaline.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B87081C0DBE70BF0232120685DF1F32D" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FD9E85210552309827E87FF0F2081970" pageNumber="5">
Distribution: Known only from the type locality, temporary pools near stream close to Rio 
<normalizedToken id="0DEB9641FD61970BEDD32026945E5763" originalValue="Uatumã">Uatuma</normalizedToken>
, Rio Amazonas basin, central Amazon, northern Brazil. Rio 
<normalizedToken id="CCE3D6E4398A70BD7F860FB155B446DF" originalValue="Uatumã">Uatuma</normalizedToken>
is a northern tributary of the Rio Amazonas, placed between Rio Negro and Rio Trombetas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="38BD9EB4C23C158DCC26079E62D18154" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="2D20328A37D8F4C8BCE654E78DDB5DC1" pageNumber="5">Habitat notes: All the specimens of the type series were collected in isolated temporary pools within the Amazonian forest. The pools were located near the forest border (Fig. 3) and were shallow (about 3-15 cm deep). The bottom was litter and the water dark tea colored, becoming turbid after collection (Fig. 4).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A89E1F8D51A91348EFB18C641C214A31" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="A9E6D71F3BC0839DCC1E4600DD5ECDD7" pageNumber="5">
Etymology: The name uatuman refers to the river basin in which the new species was collected. The name is probably derived from the local language of the Waimiri-Atroari, linguistic group Karib, an indigenous tribe of people inhabiting Rio 
<normalizedToken id="F9AA68A478D58552E78B5C4AD16680B8" originalValue="Uatumã">Uatuma</normalizedToken>
and adjacent river basins.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7632761A2D123843ED6E6D57E15385E9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B5B1C087F6D3110280DD99F9711D5569" pageNumber="6">Discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="143AE938BA5C7B5CCC47C04ACEABE282" pageNumber="6">
Characters of the cephalic latero-sensory system and frontal squamation have been consistently employed in the systematics of cyprinodontiform fishes. Gosline (1949) described the latero-sensory system of the head in the fundulid genus 
<taxonomicName id="827F44D8058457E5B463AE8DC3566BC7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:9D375722-F672-4C0C-9BC1-9E8FDFE1E488" class="Actinopterygii" family="Fundulidae" genus="Fundulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Fundulus Lacépède 1803:37" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
Fundulus 
<normalizedToken id="AA34DD57F05041A0E3530B5ACCE081A8" originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
</taxonomicName>
, providing interesting comparisons with other cyprinodontiform taxa. Subsequently, Hoedeman (1958) described the frontal scale patterns in some cyprinodontiforms, establishing a new terminology based on the frontal squamation in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="3D29FFA89F85C8BB20FBF02DC2DF108D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus Poey</taxonomicName>
. Since then, both characters of the cephalic laterosensory system and the frontal squamation have been used in systematic studies of different cyprinodontiform groups, including poeciliids (e.g., Rosen &amp; Mendelson, 1960), fundulids (e.g., Wiley, 1977), and rivulids (e. g., Costa, 1998, 2001). In rivulids, however, these traits are highly modified. The frontal scales are reduced and primarily arranged in a circular pattern, and all cephalic canals are opened or absent and consequently represented by exposed neuromasts (e.g., Parenti, 1981; Costa, 1998, 2004a).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8422F251CE2E0F59AD86733CED9D7B98" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8252B1CF03147574932E9DA8D36B14E9" lastPageNumber="7" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="429BCFD2572F40D724238AFC41688081" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:857D199C-C21E-4B3B-83BD-E2EDFDD3260F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uatuman Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uatuman">Rivulus uatuman</taxonomicName>
possesses an uncommon pattern of frontal squamation, already reported and illustrated for a few species of 
<taxonomicName id="2377D246F2006E2419BBAF0B54BCCEB6" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
by some authors (e.g., Fels &amp; de Rham, 1982; Thomerson et al, 1992; Costa, 2003b, 2004b) (Fig. 5A). This pattern consists of one scale with all the margins exposed and placed just posterior to the snout, instead of the frontal scale with all margins exposed being positioned near the center of the frontal region (Fig. 5B) as in other rivulids. This unique pattern is present in 
<taxonomicName id="3697AF37A0EF17F209C57F12894B5B3A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:34603111-87BE-467C-8532-236E69A386BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus amanapira Costa 2004:7" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amanapira">R. amanapira</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="093A42832E8D2100271EFB3E12D1BDB7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3449F866-C045-4154-92A0-F9A956507FD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus atratus Garman 1895:140" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="atratus">R. atratus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6A35DA645ED60E7C826DD57B058158FF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:8750C858-4799-4685-9B2F-41CE4CA3B9B7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus ornatus Garman 1895:139" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ornatus">R. ornatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="02AD37CFB5613F59401E329E130A55D0" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D9B00C70-6F1F-497B-984A-F96A732C5DD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus kirovskyi Costa 2004:10" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">R. kirovskyi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D68A9FA16A84EDC1788A42D9E11D162B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:65F512B3-6450-4C16-8292-22BECCD09F81" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus rectocaudatus Fels &amp; de Rham 1981:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rectocaudatus">R. rectocaudatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0199D9A6346EA794B7542E943E586E41" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="46673A71C9382AFF4F001486BAB62FF1" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F695CCB-F36C-4D87-A484-3D422BB7A184" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus tecminae Thomerson, Nico &amp; Taphorn 1992:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tecminae">R. tecminae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="43CA150A3EDED425F5B516336863D5DF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:89EFDDE7-71EC-4FC4-B295-D3A3013FE4C6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uakti Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uakti">R. uakti</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="6624316EAE3D08DE6039AFB2CA105B16" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:857D199C-C21E-4B3B-83BD-E2EDFDD3260F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uatuman Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uatuman">R. uatuman</taxonomicName>
, all of these species also sharing a derived color pattern in which there is a distinctive infraorbital dark gray bar through the chin (Costa, 2003b, 2004b). In addition, the frontal scales are arranged transversely (Fig. 5A), instead of circularly as in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="E95724E4BDF74F89D01FD7CE33B48C4D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 5B), only in 
<taxonomicName id="806CA924FA53FDEFCA28A57B22C55FAC" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:34603111-87BE-467C-8532-236E69A386BF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus amanapira Costa 2004:7" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="amanapira">R. amanapira</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="77F04F581F0BAD3F69DE779852E22039" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D9B00C70-6F1F-497B-984A-F96A732C5DD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus kirovskyi Costa 2004:10" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">R. kirovskyi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="68052BE7B817E01F0759DC0B93F379CA" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:65F512B3-6450-4C16-8292-22BECCD09F81" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus rectocaudatus Fels &amp; de Rham 1981:66" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rectocaudatus">R. rectocaudatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CB245822BE6087C5243DB335A6BAB294" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0E9866B315705537D4F34CADA4E09F49" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2F695CCB-F36C-4D87-A484-3D422BB7A184" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus tecminae Thomerson, Nico &amp; Taphorn 1992:290" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tecminae">R. tecminae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F1AB27F10F17038D1B097A5CB9691ECD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:89EFDDE7-71EC-4FC4-B295-D3A3013FE4C6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uakti Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uakti">R. uakti</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="48825AFE59F80854E5CCD6E82EA92A7B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:857D199C-C21E-4B3B-83BD-E2EDFDD3260F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uatuman Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="6" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uatuman">R. uatuman</taxonomicName>
. These species also exhibit some other unique apomorphic conditions such as the absence of dermosphenotic and absence of preopercular canal (Costa, 2003b, 2004b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="77B528BE001B56FCAE1DBC6F16A5C807" pageNumber="7">
A unique arrangement of supraorbital neuromasts is present in 
<taxonomicName id="3D96859C5A652460E26CA89C12EA69E7" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D9B00C70-6F1F-497B-984A-F96A732C5DD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus kirovskyi Costa 2004:10" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">R. kirovskyi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="9E2ED7291E09D76097F10B1100D98B5B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="06EB7A8EE8F3938D3618BB1A8F689503" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:857D199C-C21E-4B3B-83BD-E2EDFDD3260F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uatuman Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uatuman">R. uatuman</taxonomicName>
. In these species, the third neuromast of the anterior supraorbital series is separated from the two anterior neuromasts by an interspace occupied by one scale (Fig. 5A), in contrast to all three supraorbital neuromasts forming a continuous row (Fig. 5B). The putative monophyly of the group comprising 
<taxonomicName id="FF0A08D0F2190AEE111D91C50350570B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:D9B00C70-6F1F-497B-984A-F96A732C5DD5" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus kirovskyi Costa 2004:10" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kirovskyi">Rivulus kirovskyi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F9A775E7C2D083D028DEE53DAEBBA5EB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:3F82970E-059D-4190-BBBB-3CEAA8DF4B99" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus romeri Costa 2003:176" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="romeri">R. romeri</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="1E9167AC1E083FB880E6E287E15BE6BD" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:857D199C-C21E-4B3B-83BD-E2EDFDD3260F" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus uatuman Costa 2004:2" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="uatuman">R. uatuman</taxonomicName>
is also corroborated by other characters. Besides constituting the smallest species of the genus, reaching 22.7 mm SL as maximum adult size, these three species also share the absence of vomerine teeth, a condition not occurring in basal rivulid genera (
<taxonomicName id="1EC5619C7A84B058C69F028655FA9820" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:94FD1A9A-96E4-4EFE-820B-1313C8AB57F6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Kryptolebias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Kryptolebias Costa 2004" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Kryptolebias Costa</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="69A6A269B50327A93AC81763627D24B8" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F529EA97-6B29-4000-8107-85555FB2973E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Prorivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Prorivulus Costa 2004:3" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Prorivulus Costa</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="57E3D065DF5DF00B1314AF356F5F8C3D" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:7737CC47-FB47-4DAF-87C2-18950BAD40FA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Rivulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Rivulus Poey 1860:307" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="7" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rivulus</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
